    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Patenôtre</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">M. Patenôtre</hi>,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister of France,<lb/>On board “La Bretagne,” New York:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I am informed by the governor of Pennsylvania that the police officer who offered
                    the insult to the French flag at Jeannette, Pa., has been dismissed by the town
                    officials. The delay in his dismissal was occasioned by the fact that he was an
                    elected officer.</p>
                <p>It gives me great pleasure to convey to you the notification of so satisfactory a
                    termination of this unfortunate incident.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
